  abstract={The study presents a trainable oscillatory neural network model of brain dynamics with two stages: an oscillatory stage and a complex-valued feedforward stage. The model uses power coupling to model brain connectivity and can accurately simulate functional connectivity with a correlation coefficient of 0.99. It can also identify default mode network regions and examine how structural brain loss impacts functional connectivity. This novel power coupling approach provides an alternative to traditional linear coupling methods for modeling whole brain dynamics.},
