  abstract={The paper explores using low-power oscillatory neural networks (ONNs) for edge detection on edge devices. The authors introduce two novel architectures - a two-layer bidirectional ONN and a two-layer feedforward ONN - to perform image edge detection. They validate their methods using both a Matlab emulator and a digital ONN design, testing on black and white and grayscale images with different filter sizes (3×3, 5×5, and 7×7). The research demonstrates that these ONN architectures can effectively detect edges, with the feedforward architecture showing particular promise for grayscale image processing.},
